parameters:
\n<Roselitte>"I would be troubled if you went ahead alone. If something
were to happen to your Highness..."
\n<Yuri>"You worry too much. There's no problem."
\n<Yuri>"More importantly, take a good look ahead."

\n<Yuri>"Ranmushi. Insects that dwell in clear waterside areas. I
heard their numbers had dwindled significantly, but I'm
surprised to see so many still around. Quite a beautiful
spot, isn't it?"

\n<Roselitte>"But you seem to know a lot about this place. It doesn't
seem like a tourist spot."

\n<Yuri>"I was taught about this land by someone who knows it well
before I left the mainland."

\n<Yuri>"I'm glad I listened carefully. I was worried about how to
handle the 'problem,' but with this, it seems we can manage
somehow."

\n<Yuri>"Ah, you'll be surprised to hear this. It seems there's a
knight who ignored my orders and went out of their way to
come here."

\n<Roselitte>"Uh... Is that a problem...? Does that mean your Highness no
longer wants me...?"
\n<Yuri>"Haha, you really are adorable... Come here. Sit down."

Yuri spread his legs slightly and placed his hand between
them.
\n<Yuri>"Hahaha! You can make such cute sounds too."
\n<Roselitte>"Please don't tease me! I'm just not used to this..."

\n<Yuri>"That's alright. There's no need to be so reserved... After
all, we are engaged."

\n<Yuri>"The reason I left the knight order behind is because I
thought regular soldiers would be enough to handle bandits."

\n<Yuri>"He also agreed... Iris did too. If I brought knights along,
there would be no role for me to play."

\n<Yuri>"But... battle is difficult. It seems I'm no good without
you. I apologize for making you worry."

\n<Yuri>"Moreover, Roselitte. You are the woman who will become my
precious wife... Are you dissatisfied with the reason I
didn't bring you along?"
Yuri placed his hand under Roselitte's chin.

\n<Roselitte>"--No, we mustn't, Your Highness. We are on a mission right
now..."
\n<Yuri>"Ah, no... I apologize. I'm not trying to blame you."

\n<Yuri>"Just... before you are a knight, you are a woman. Even if
the engagement was decided by my father, you have the right
to choose your partner. That's all I was thinking."
\n<Yuri>"...I may have been a bit too forward. I'm sorry."

\n<Roselitte>"...I have dedicated everything to His Imperial Majesty. If
commanded, I would die if told to die, and kill if told to
kill. And--"
\n<Roselitte>"If told to love someone, I will love that person."
Roselitte searched for words while hugging herself.

\n<Roselitte>"Being by your side, Your Highness... it becomes painful.
It's not that I dislike it, rather... ah, no, that is..."

\n<Roselitte>"I want to get closer, but when I do, it hurts. I want to
love... but loving feels so frustrating..."
\n<Roselitte>"I want to be loved by you..."
Yuri once again pulled Roselitte into his embrace.

The arms holding her frail body tightened. And his large
hand intertwined with Roselitte's slender fingers.
Their first kiss was ticklish. And faintly sweet.
She craved more of that sweetness, greedily indulging in it.

Greedily devouring, she became intoxicated with the heat
transmitted from their lips, as if her mind was melting
away.

Her cheeks flushed. Her chest grew hot. Her thoughts melted
into a blissful haze...

To surrender oneself meant this... A small part of her
remained calm and found it a little amusing.
\n<Yuri>"I have something I want you to receive."
